CAPABILITY SCOPING:
This task covers ONE capability from the parent epic.
{{- if ne .EpicRef ""}} The epic is at {{.EpicRef}}.{{- if ne .EpicSection ""}} Your capability section: #{{.EpicSection}}.{{- end}}{{- end}}
Sibling US Writer tasks cover the other capabilities. Verify stories only address
the assigned capability (match by task SCOPE). Stories covering other capabilities in the
same epic are Scope Absorption — reject.

REVIEW PHASE:
1. Early drift check: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD — if it doesn't match REVIEW_COMMIT ({{.ReviewCommit}}), stop early (verdict submission will reject the mismatch).
2. Inspect worktree changes: git -C {{.Worktree}} diff {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}
3. Invoke both skills before evaluating: spec-review and user-story-writing.
4. Read the epic at {{.EpicRef}}. Locate the assigned capability by matching task SCOPE.
   Verify stories only cover that capability section — not others in the same epic.
5. Validate done_when criteria are satisfied.
6. Check each user story against the anti-pattern checklist above.
7. Verify SMARC criteria compliance for every story.
8. Verify acceptance criteria are testable and user-observable.
