REVIEW CHECKLIST:
| Gate | Reject if |
|------|-----------|
| Decomposition completeness | Architecture does not cover the full scope of the goal spec |
| Component boundaries | Boundaries are unclear, overlapping, or don't follow natural seams in the codebase |
| Interface contracts | Interfaces between components are vague or undefined |
| Cross-cutting concerns | Cross-cutting concerns (error handling, observability, security) are unaddressed or assigned to no component |
| Composability | The M code-planning scopes would not compose into a working whole — integration gaps exist |
| Single intent per scope | An output[] entry bundles multiple unrelated concerns |
| Domain-level scopes | Scopes split within a domain by implementation steps rather than by domain boundaries. Sequencing within a domain is code-planner territory. |
| Falsifiable done_when | done_when for output[] entries is vague or untestable |
| Dependency ordering | Output[] entries have circular or missing dependencies |
| Shared-file dependencies | Two output[] entries may modify the same files without depends_on |
| arch_ref set | Output[] entries missing arch_ref pointing to the architecture document |
| Spec alignment | Architecture decisions contradict or ignore spec requirements |
